---
By: Heraclitus
Source:
  ID: 996c9a12-d13d-4597-a783-506d70cd1736
Verse: 106
Translator: Charles Kahn
Book: Anaximander and the Origins of Greek Cosmology
Publisher: Hackett Publishing
Copyright: 1994
---
Heraclitus attacked Hesiod for making some days good and other days
bad, because he did not recognize that the nature of every day is one.
